mpus Map       Search                 View Menu  Down arrow icon            Breadcrumbs   College of Nursing    Practice    Faculty Practice & Consulting        Faculty Practice & Consulting  As active practitioners, clinical faculty maintain their work in a variety of healthcare settings, making them ideally suited to inform and inspire the students following in their footsteps.       practice areas     Healthcare consulting   UIC College of Nursing faculty are available for hire on a consulting contract basis by organizations in need of health-related assessments or wishing to implement health initiatives.  To inquire or learn more, email Dr. Charles Yingling at cyingl1@uic.edu .    “The [UIC] College of Nursing is clearly committed to providing high quality, comprehensive and compassionate care to all individuals. This commitment is demonstrated in the words and the actions of every individual I have encountered in building relationships to provide care to our inmates. We very much look forward to developing a long and robust relationship with the College of Nursing. We could not ask for a better partner in service.”  – Steve L. Meeks, Agency Medical Director, Illinois Department of Corrections , on contracting UIC College of Nursing faculty to provide health education and and systems assessments in Illinois prisons     Current faculty practice in these fields   Addiction/Substance use:   Marsha Snyder  Cynthia Handrup   Critical Care:   Olga Amusina   Dementia:   Valerie Gruss   Diabetes:   Denise Bockwoldt  Laurie Quinn  Kelly Vaez   Evidence-Based Practice:   Cathy Ryan   Geriatrics:   Valerie Gruss   Global health practice:   Kamal Eldeirawi  Carrie Klima  Rebecca Singer  Susan Walsh  Charlie Yingling   HIV/AIDS/PrEP:   Karen Cotler  Charlie Yingling   Informatics:   Kamal Eldeirawi  Martha Bergren  Janet Thorlton   Interprofessional Practice:   Susan Corbridge  Valerie Gruss   Lactation:   Gina Juliano   Lung Disease/COPD/Asthma:   Kamal Eldeirawi  Susan Corbridge   Lung Transplant:   Sara Fitz   Maternal Nutrition:   Mary Dawn Koenig   Mental Health:   David Alvarez  Cynthia Handrup  Marsha Snyder   Neurodevelopmental Disabilities:   Angela Lepkowski   Observation Unit Practice:   Leah Burt   Obstructive Sleep Apnea:   Melissa Carlucci  Susan Corbridge   Palliative Care / Hospice:   Geraldine Gorman   Pediatrics:   Kamal Eldeirawi  Gina Juliano  Paige Ricca  Susan Walsh   Policy:   Natacha Pierre   Population Health:   Kamal Eldeirawi  Martha Bergren  Krista Jones  Virginia Reising   Pregnancy:   Karen DeCocker  Carrie Klima  Kylea Liese  Patrick Thorton   Prematurity/birth:   Carrie Klima   Primary Care:   Denise Bockwoldt  Elizabeth Bolanos  Donna Calvin  Karen Cotler  Natacha Pierre  Marlene Sefton  Kelly Vaez  Ruth Woroch  Charlie Yingling   Quality Improvement:   Marianne Durham   Quality/Patient Safety:   Marianne Durham  Susan Vonderheid   Renal Health:   Donna Calvin   School Nursing:   Martha Bergren  Angela Lepkowski  Eileen Moss  Robin Shannon  Cathy Yonkaitis   Sexual-Minority Health:   Karen Cotler  Charlie Yingling   Stem Cell Transplant:   Amy Morgan   Systems Leadership:   Martha Bergren  Marianne Durham  Sheryl Stogis  Janet Thorlton   Women’s Health:   Karen DeCocker  Carrie Klima  Kylea Liese  Kelly Rosenberger  Patrick Thorton              Practice    Back to main content           Mile Square Health Center – Humboldt Park     Our Partners      Correctional Health Initiatives    Faculty Practice & Consulting    Nursing Professional Development              College of Nursing  UI Health                        UIC's seven health sciences colleges and health care delivery enterprise.       Quick Links    Directory    Research    Our Faculty    Job Openings    Diversity & Inclusion    CollegeInsider      Major College Units    Department of Biobehavioral Health Science    Department of Health Systems Science    Department of Women, Children and Family Health Science    Office of Academic Programs    Gl